SOUTHAMPTON Liverpool showed signs of fatigue in their 2-1 win over Southampton at St Mary's on Saturday. Fresh from winning the Uefa Super Cup on Wednesday, Liverpool opened the scoring just before the break through Sadio Mane's whose curler flew into the top right corner. Roberto Firmino added a second in the 71st minute in what was a moment of individual brilliance before Adrian gifted former Liverpool striker Danny Ings in the 83rd for the Saints' consolation. More to follow...  